In First chapter titled "The Three Rules of epidemics", writer refers to three principle key:
The law of the few, the stickiness factor, The power of context. 
First, The law of the few means 20% of something maked a 80% of work (etc. job, crimesâ€¦).
In this book, few people had sex with others, so they spread HIV(AIDS) to others. 
Second, the Stickiness Factor refers to how memorable or persistent an idea or behavior is.
Lastly, The power of context means that context influences the result.
The author gives an example of bystander problem.
